As of now, the current service for automating *JIRA* backups only applies for an option to set the *Delay* between backups:
* [Automating JIRA Backups|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Automating+JIRA+Backups]

Is it possible to introduce another option to have the ability to *overwrite* the backup files? As an example:
# The current file in the export is {{2013-Apr-01--1655.zip}}
# After a certain period of time (Eg. setting the delay to 1 week = 10080 minutes), the {{2013-Apr-01--1655.zip}} gets overwritten rather than creating a new file {{2013-Apr-01--1656.zip}}

Of course, the user should have the ability to set the format of the file since the current one is based on the *Date* and *Time* when the .zip file is created.

This can save the disk space in the long run. Rather than having a lot of backup files, the folder will always get updated with the latest backup only.

