When the JIRA filter URL format has changed, Confluence needs to add support for the auto-conversion of the new URL format into the JIRA Issues Macro (Assuming Confluence and JIRA are applinked).

Currently there is no means of knowing when the URL format has changed and, consequently, integration fails between Confluence and JIRA. This is outlined in:
https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-27945

A test can be written which fails when a new URL format is used so Confluence can be alerted to implement support for a new URL format.

Currently the three supported formats are:
{code}
https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/IssueNavigator.jspa?reset=true&jqlQuery=project%20%3D%20CONF
{code}

and {code}
https://jira.atlassian.com/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest-xml/temp/SearchRequest.xml?jqlQuery=project+%3D+CONF
{code}

and
{code}
https://jira.atlassian.com/issues/?jql=project%20%3D%20CONF
{code}

